{
  "stem": "1183.2",
  "chunk_idx": 1,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 3.9,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "Then they entered the market, and as fast as we could, we walked over to one of the houses where we're lucky enough to know-- to have some friends there.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "There, from the window of those friend's house or flat, we watched the horror, how they were beating and taking the people into trucks and rounding the whole market up.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "And actually we were shaken.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "It took us quite a while to-- for everything was safe, so we could leave for home.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "But in the meantime, my mother was home.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 29,
      "text": "And everybody heard about the round-up.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 30,
      "text": "And she was semi-conscious when we came home, because in that time, as I said, we had no phone.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 31,
      "text": "And there was nothing to tell her that we were safe.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 32,
      "text": "When we came home, she was beside herself.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 33,
      "text": "And it took quite a time for her to come back, to get her composure.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 34,
      "text": "That was the second time that my father saved my life.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 35,
      "text": "Then also in 19-- yeah, it was 1941 or 1942, my mother was still alive.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 36,
      "text": "There was a night of bombing, English coming over.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 37,
      "text": "And I don't know if it was accidentally or what, there was a bomb falling on our neighbor's-- a couple of houses [PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] distance from us.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 38,
      "text": "And in that house, [LAUGHS] watching, naturally, families, but there was a family, family Bromet.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 39,
      "text": "And I played with the guy and his brother.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 40,
      "text": "And his name was Harry Bromet.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 41,
      "text": "And he was born on the same date, the same year as my husband, who is also Harry Bromet, which is a very coincidence.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 42,
      "text": "That boy was killed at that night.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 43,
      "text": "That is one of the freak things from life that later on I happen to marry Harry Bromet.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 44,
      "text": "It's the same thing.",
      "word_count": 4
    }
  ],
